'''''Apostate capiendo''''' (Latin for "taking an apostate")<ref>[http://legaldictionary.lawin.org/de-apostata-capiendo/ "de apostate capiendo" Legal Dictionaries of the Encyclopedia of Law Project]</ref> was an old [[England|English]] [[writ]] against an individual. It prescribed the arrest of a person, who having entered and professed some [[religious order]] (such as a [[monk]]), broke from his [[cloister]], contrary to the rules of his order.<ref>[http://legaldictionary.lawin.org/apostata-capiendo/ "apostata capiendo" Legal Dictionaries of the Encyclopedia of Law Project]</ref><ref>{{1728}}</ref>

