'''Entwurf eines Cannabiskontrollgesetzes''' (CannKG) ("design of a cannabis control law") is a proposed descheduling of [[cannabis]] from [[Betäubungsmittelgesetz]], the federal controlled substances law in Germany. The issue was proposed by [[Alliance '90/The Greens]] (the German Green Party). It would regulate cannabis in a manner similar to alcohol, with adults 18 years old permitted to buy and possess up to 30 grams in regulated stores.<ref name=Spiegel2015/><ref name=Welt2015/>

