{{Infobox university |name = West Bengal Judicial Academy |image = West Bengal Judicial Academy 05.jpg |image_size = | motto = |established = 2005 |type = Registered Society <!-- [[Governmental organization|GO]], [[Non-governmental organization|NGO]], [[Intergovernmental organization|IGO]], [[International nongovernmental organization|INGO]], etc --> |director = |city = {{Flag icon|India}} [[Kolkata]] |state = [[West Bengal]] |country = [[India]] |campus = [[urban area|Urban]] |website = |logo = |affiliations = Calcutta High Court |faculty = |Admin Staff = }} {{Courts of India}} '''West Bengal Judicial Academy''' is a training institution for the Judges of the Indian state of [[West Bengal]] and officers of the [[West Bengal Judicial Service]]. The institution organises Induction Level Training for newly appointed Judicial Officers as well as entry level District Judges of West Bengal.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.wbja.nic.in/|title=West Bengal Judicial Academy|last=|first=|date=|website=wbja.nic.in|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=August 26, 2018}}</ref> ==History== The [[Law Commission of India]] recommended to establish Judicial academies in various state of [[India]] for training of all Judges of the subordinate Judiciary. Subsequently the [[Supreme Court of India]] accepted those recommendations and on 28 February [[Calcutta High Court]] issued a notification to set up a state Judicial Academy under the name of West Bengal Judicial Academy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wbja.nic.in/wbja_adm/files/Establishment.pdf|title=The Kolkata Gazette|last=|first=|date=June 14, 2005|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=August 26, 2018}}</ref> On 3 September 2005, the [[Chief Justice of India]] Mr. Justice [[Y.K. Sabharwal]] inaugurated the Academy in [[Kolkata]].<ref name=":0" /> Initially it was started in Bijan Bhwan, [[Bidhannagar]] but latter transferred to a new campus of [[Rajarhat]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/1021026/asp/calcutta/story_1324546.asp|title=From abode of judges to guest house|last=|first=|date=|website=telegraphindia.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=August 26, 2018}}</ref> ==See also== * [[National Judicial Academy (India)]] * [[National Law University and Judicial Academy, Assam]]
